Definition: in a grievous manner
Example: the resolute but unbroken Germany, grievously wounded but far from destruction, was able to lay the firm foundations for military revival
Synonyms: adj, all, critical, grievous, in, a, manner, the, resolute, but, unbroken, Germany, wounded, far, from, destruction, was, able, to, lay, firm, foundations, for, military, revival
Category: adv.all
